# Google Cloud OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application type), used for the
# "Connect Google Account" / vendor email-send feature. No client secret is
# needed — this app uses the browser-only Google Identity Services token
# client (gmail.send scope), not a server-side OAuth flow.
#
# Setup: Google Cloud Console → new/existing project → enable the Gmail API
# → OAuth consent screen (add scopes gmail.send + userinfo.email, add your
# Google account as a test user, leave in Testing mode) → Credentials →
# Create OAuth client ID → Web application → Authorized JavaScript origins:
# http://localhost:5173 (add your production origin later too).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
